Result: false  
Justification:  
The P-type arguments do not cover all minimal semantic bases for the claim "Dimples enjoys cool temperatures." Specifically, the claim is directly addressed by the given exclusive disjunction: "Either Dimples enjoys cool temperatures or she prefers warm temperatures, but not both." The minimal semantic basis for the claim would require establishing that Dimples does not prefer warm temperatures, but none of the P-type arguments provide justification for ruling out the warm preference alternative. Instead, they rely on indirect inferences (e.g., feeling hot, not staying cool) that do not conclusively eliminate the possibility that Dimples prefers warm temperatures. Since C11 requires that for every minimal semantic basis of the claim, there exists a P-type argument whose justification contains that basis, and here a necessary basis (negation of the alternative) is missing, C11 is not satisfied.